					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jack-ike" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1618170); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1618170&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251148" alt="Jack Ike" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1618170)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jack-ike" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1618170); return false;" >Jack Ike</a></span> <span class="odate time_1491359070 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 Apr 2017 02:24</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2783888">
									

<p>Damn it Roget, you've put me between a rock and a hard place.</p>
<p>Fundamentally, I love this GOI document. I love that someone is finally trying to give Alexylva one, I love the idea you went for what it is.</p>
<p>But I do not think the actual content fits. The image I got of Alexylva from the skips I've read was of a colossal, Neo-Ancient Greek school.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-641906-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-641906-1')">1</a></sup> This reads more along the lines of a Oneiroi district based upon Greece - it repeatedly claims to be focused on knowledge and learning, but then incessantly cites these weird and blatantly nonsensical rituals throughout it that, again, feel vastly more fitting in a Oneiroi setting.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-641906-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-641906-2')">2</a></sup></p>
<p>Again, I love the presentation and idea of this Alexylva GOI document, but the actual content fits far, far better with the Oneiroi than Alexylva.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-641906-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-641906-1')">1</a>. I know 'Neo-Ancient' doesn't make sense. I mean something along the lines of 'Ancient Greece, but cyberpunk-ish'. Modern/Advanced/Futuristic technology in the setting of Ancient Greece.</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-641906-2"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-641906-2')">2</a>. 'DOUSE THEM IN THE CLEANSING LIQUID OF THOUGHT,' 'DISCOVER HOW TO PLUMB THE MIND IN OTHERS TO FACILITATE LIFE ADVANTAGE,' 'JUDGEMENT WILL BE MADE ON CRYING OUT TO THE INFINITE UNKNOWN AND WILLINGNESS TO PROSELYTIZE THE SELF BEFORE THE YAWNING VOID,' etc.</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
					
